        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">No enrage is necessary.  Mobs just like our pets now.</P><P>I'm having the same problem in the Dreadlands.  Taunting warrior, rogue doing absurd damage, wizard burning things down, cleric doing complete heals, who gets the aggro?  My untaunting pet.  And if that pet ever gets down to around 30% health, just get ready to summon a new one, ain't nothin' gonna taunt the mob off.</P><P>Weirdly enough, my shaman doesn't have any trouble at all keeping his pet alive in a group, it rarely gets beat on.</P><P>My guess is that the AI change to invulnerability skewed the whole targeting choice system.  If the AI is trying to eliminate the most damage first, the scoring might conceptually be something like...</P><P>(estimated damage in x seconds) / ((weighted AC) * (weighted HP))</P><P>...with taunting adding in to the damage portion and doing other funky things.    Unfortunately, that would make our high-damage, low AC (compared to the tanks), low HP (comparatively) pets enemy number one.</P><P>Somebody add it to the nerf list...</P><P><b>Morty Undercrypt</b>, Keeper of the <font color=red>NecroGnomicon</font id=red><BR><small>"Whoops, was I supposed to be taking names too?"</small><BR>E'ci<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
